{"type":"file-history-snapshot","messageId":"60099a69-3877-4cd9-b8f8-37b3f7d26a60","snapshot":{"messageId":"0ae77f10-4f3c-4c2f-b298-4f2a62273ae0","trackedFileBackups":{"Desktop\\DSC_INDIA_1\\KY FRT CUSH\\S50\\FrmToolPos.vb":{"backupFileName":"b384fd65f08e2562@v4","version":4,"backupTime":"2026-02-26T23:56:57.865Z"},"Desktop\\DSC_INDIA_1\\KY FRT CUSH\\S50\\FrmToolPos.Designer.vb":{"backupFileName":"f392a56615d9a79f@v3","version":3,"backupTime":"2026-02-26T23:56:57.867Z"},"Desktop\\DSC_INDIA_1\\KY FRT CUSH\\S50\\FrmToolPos.resx":{"backupFileName":"519ffecedd9a98d5@v2","version":2,"backupTime":"2026-02-26T23:41:53.194Z"},"Desktop\\DSC_INDIA_1\\KY FRT CUSH\\S50\\S50(192.168.0.36).vbproj":{"backupFileName":"b444b9e224f223f1@v2","version":2,"backupTime":"2026-02-26T23:41:53.196Z"},"Desktop\\DSC_INDIA_1\\KY FRT CUSH\\S50\\FrmMain.vb":{"backupFileName":"70ab66ce18bdc49a@v4","version":4,"backupTime":"2026-02-26T23:56:57.870Z"},"Desktop\\TighteningPositionSetup_UserGuide.md":{"backupFileName":null,"version":1,"backupTime":"2026-02-26T23:57:37.139Z"}},"timestamp":"2026-02-26T23:56:57.862Z"},"isSnapshotUpdate":true}
{"parentUuid":"b2c95f52-fd12-4b87-87b1-ad2e9a2f46bb","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator","sessionId":"e91f03cf-3406-4976-ac29-0eb1468a27b4","version":"2.1.59","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"glimmering-shimmying-boole","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Apwzmz9csVwGzrdo3xaA7k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RxTG8L4DnDZ9qgw7JNbFKZ","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\TighteningPositionSetup_UserGuide.md","content":"# Tightening Position Setup – User Guide\n\n---\n\n## What is this screen for?\n\nThis screen is used to **set the tightening positions (P1 to P5) for each spec** on the assembly image.\nOnce set, the positions will be displayed as numbered circles on the main screen during production.\n\n---\n\n## How to Open\n\nClick the **Setup** button on the main screen.\nThe \"Tightening Position Setup\" window will appear.\n\n---\n\n## Step-by-Step Instructions\n\n### Step 1 – Select a Spec\n\n![Spec Select](step1)\n\n- Click the **Spec Select** dropdown at the top right.\n- Choose the spec you want to edit (e.g. `HGT_LH_QY`, `NHGT_RH_KY`, etc.).\n- The image and coordinates for that spec will load automatically.\n\n> **Note:** There are 8 specs in total. Each spec has its own image and positions.\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 – Select an Image\n\n- Click the **\"Select Image\"** button.\n- A file browser window will open.\n- Navigate to the assembly image file and click **Open**.\n- The image will appear in the preview area on the left.\n\n> Supported formats: `.bmp`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.png`, `.gif`\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 – Set Tightening Positions (P1 to P5)\n\nYou can set positions in two ways:\n\n#### Method A – Click on the Image (Recommended)\n\n1. In the **Tightening Position** box, select the radio button next to **P1**.\n2. **Click on the image** at the exact location of tightening point No.1.\n   → The X and Y coordinates will be filled in automatically.\n   → The selection automatically moves to **P2**.\n3. Continue clicking for P2, P3, P4, P5 in order.\n\n#### Method B – Enter Coordinates Manually\n\n- Type the **X** and **Y** values directly into the boxes next to each point (P1 to P5).\n- The circles on the preview image will update in real time.\n\n> **Tip:** You can mix both methods — click to place, then fine-tune by typing.\n\n---\n\n### Step 4 – Adjust Circle Size (Optional)\n\n- The **Circle Size (px)** field controls how large the numbered circles appear on the main screen.\n- Default value is **30**.\n- Increase the number for a larger circle, decrease for smaller.\n- The number font size inside the circle adjusts automatically.\n\n---\n\n### Step 5 – Save\n\n- When all positions look correct in the preview, click **Save**.\n- A message \"Saved successfully.\" will appear.\n- Click **OK** to confirm.\n\n---\n\n### Step 6 – Close\n\n- Click **Close** to exit the setup screen.\n- You can reopen it at any time to make changes.\n\n---\n\n## Screen Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Tightening Position Setup                               [X] │\n├───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                       │  Spec Select                        │\n│                       │  [ HGT_LH_QY            ▼ ]        │\n│                       │                                     │\n│   Assembly Image      │  Image Path                         │\n│   (Preview)           │  [________________] [Select Image]  │\n│                       │                                     │\n│   ● Circles appear    │  Tightening Position                │\n│     here after        │  ● P1  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n│     positions are     │  ○ P2  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n│     set               │  ○ P3  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n│                       │  ○ P4  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n│                       │  ○ P5  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n│                       │                                     │\n│                       │  Circle Size (px): [30]             │\n│                       │                                     │\n│                       │  * Click image to set coordinate    │\n├───────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                              [  Save  ]     [  Close  ]     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Spec Name Reference\n\n| Spec Name     | Description                        |\n|---------------|------------------------------------|\n| HGT_LH_QY     | HGT / Left Hand / QY model         |\n| HGT_LH_KY     | HGT / Left Hand / KY model         |\n| HGT_RH_QY     | HGT / Right Hand / QY model        |\n| HGT_RH_KY     | HGT / Right Hand / KY model        |\n| NHGT_LH_QY    | N/HGT / Left Hand / QY model       |\n| NHGT_LH_KY    | N/HGT / Left Hand / KY model       |\n| NHGT_RH_QY    | N/HGT / Right Hand / QY model      |\n| NHGT_RH_KY    | N/HGT / Right Hand / KY model      |\n\n---\n\n## Important Notes\n\n- **Always click Save** after making changes. Unsaved changes will be lost when you close.\n- Each spec must be set up **separately**. Changing one spec does not affect others.\n- If the image file is moved or deleted, the image will not appear. Use **Select Image** to re-link it.\n- Coordinates are based on the **original image size**, not the preview size.\n\n---\n\n*For any issues, contact your system administrator.*\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1856,"cache_read_input_tokens":102793,"output_tokens":1991,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1856,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CYXaw2WLF2seZyhUqXdtE","type":"assistant","uuid":"60099a69-3877-4cd9-b8f8-37b3f7d26a60","timestamp":"2026-02-26T23:57:37.137Z"}
