{"parentUuid":"6ef16c4b-de82-46f9-85ca-772197e037e3","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator","sessionId":"e91f03cf-3406-4976-ac29-0eb1468a27b4","version":"2.1.59","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"glimmering-shimmying-boole","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Bk4ZozLPDDbVLWV3xg5tSo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Tightening Position Setup – User Guide\n     2→\n     3→---\n     4→\n     5→## What is this screen for?\n     6→\n     7→This screen is used to **set the tightening positions (P1 to P5) for each spec** on the assembly image.\n     8→Once set, the positions will be displayed as numbered circles on the main screen during production.\n     9→\n    10→---\n    11→\n    12→## How to Open\n    13→\n    14→Click the **Setup** button on the main screen.\n    15→The \"Tightening Position Setup\" window will appear.\n    16→\n    17→---\n    18→\n    19→## Step-by-Step Instructions\n    20→\n    21→### Step 1 – Select a Spec\n    22→\n    23→![Spec Select](step1)\n    24→\n    25→- Click the **Spec Select** dropdown at the top right.\n    26→- Choose the spec you want to edit (e.g. `HGT_LH_QY`, `NHGT_RH_KY`, etc.).\n    27→- The image and coordinates for that spec will load automatically.\n    28→\n    29→> **Note:** There are 8 specs in total. Each spec has its own image and positions.\n    30→\n    31→---\n    32→\n    33→### Step 2 – Select an Image\n    34→\n    35→- Click the **\"Select Image\"** button.\n    36→- A file browser window will open.\n    37→- Navigate to the assembly image file and click **Open**.\n    38→- The image will appear in the preview area on the left.\n    39→\n    40→> Supported formats: `.bmp`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.png`, `.gif`\n    41→\n    42→---\n    43→\n    44→### Step 3 – Set Tightening Positions (P1 to P5)\n    45→\n    46→You can set positions in two ways:\n    47→\n    48→#### Method A – Click on the Image (Recommended)\n    49→\n    50→1. In the **Tightening Position** box, select the radio button next to **P1**.\n    51→2. **Click on the image** at the exact location of tightening point No.1.\n    52→   → The X and Y coordinates will be filled in automatically.\n    53→   → The selection automatically moves to **P2**.\n    54→3. Continue clicking for P2, P3, P4, P5 in order.\n    55→\n    56→#### Method B – Enter Coordinates Manually\n    57→\n    58→- Type the **X** and **Y** values directly into the boxes next to each point (P1 to P5).\n    59→- The circles on the preview image will update in real time.\n    60→\n    61→> **Tip:** You can mix both methods — click to place, then fine-tune by typing.\n    62→\n    63→---\n    64→\n    65→### Step 4 – Adjust Circle Size (Optional)\n    66→\n    67→- The **Circle Size (px)** field controls how large the numbered circles appear on the main screen.\n    68→- Default value is **30**.\n    69→- Increase the number for a larger circle, decrease for smaller.\n    70→- The number font size inside the circle adjusts automatically.\n    71→\n    72→---\n    73→\n    74→### Step 5 – Save\n    75→\n    76→- When all positions look correct in the preview, click **Save**.\n    77→- A message \"Saved successfully.\" will appear.\n    78→- Click **OK** to confirm.\n    79→\n    80→---\n    81→\n    82→### Step 6 – Close\n    83→\n    84→- Click **Close** to exit the setup screen.\n    85→- You can reopen it at any time to make changes.\n    86→\n    87→---\n    88→\n    89→## Screen Overview\n    90→\n    91→```\n    92→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    93→│  Tightening Position Setup                               [X] │\n    94→├───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┤\n    95→│                       │  Spec Select                        │\n    96→│                       │  [ HGT_LH_QY            ▼ ]        │\n    97→│                       │                                     │\n    98→│   Assembly Image      │  Image Path                         │\n    99→│   (Preview)           │  [________________] [Select Image]  │\n   100→│                       │                                     │\n   101→│   ● Circles appear    │  Tightening Position                │\n   102→│     here after        │  ● P1  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n   103→│     positions are     │  ○ P2  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n   104→│     set               │  ○ P3  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n   105→│                       │  ○ P4  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n   106→│                       │  ○ P5  X: [___]  Y: [___]          │\n   107→│                       │                                     │\n   108→│                       │  Circle Size (px): [30]             │\n   109→│                       │                                     │\n   110→│                       │  * Click image to set coordinate    │\n   111→├───────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┤\n   112→│                              [  Save  ]     [  Close  ]     │\n   113→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n   114→```\n   115→\n   116→---\n   117→\n   118→## Spec Name Reference\n   119→\n   120→| Spec Name     | Description                        |\n   121→|---------------|------------------------------------|\n   122→| HGT_LH_QY     | HGT / Left Hand / QY model         |\n   123→| HGT_LH_KY     | HGT / Left Hand / KY model         |\n   124→| HGT_RH_QY     | HGT / Right Hand / QY model        |\n   125→| HGT_RH_KY     | HGT / Right Hand / KY model        |\n   126→| NHGT_LH_QY    | N/HGT / Left Hand / QY model       |\n   127→| NHGT_LH_KY    | N/HGT / Left Hand / KY model       |\n   128→| NHGT_RH_QY    | N/HGT / Right Hand / QY model      |\n   129→| NHGT_RH_KY    | N/HGT / Right Hand / KY model      |\n   130→\n   131→---\n   132→\n   133→## Important Notes\n   134→\n   135→- **Always click Save** after making changes. Unsaved changes will be lost when you close.\n   136→- Each spec